Pseudo-residual analysis for relaxed clock

Xavier Didelot

2025-07-18

We start by generating a dated tree with no structure and a small effective population size \(N_e g=1\) year relative to the sampling frame of 10 years between 2010 and 2020:

library(DiagnoDating,quietly=T)
set.seed(1)
dates=runif(100,2010,2020)
dt=simcoaltree(dates,alpha=1)
plot(dt,show.tip.label = F)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

Next we generate a phylogenetic tree using a ARC(10,5) mutation model:

tree=simobsphy(dt,mu=10,sigma=5,model='arc')
plot(tree,show.tip.label = F)
axisPhylo(1,backward=F)

A root-to-tip regression analysis works not so well:

res=roottotip(tree,dates)

Run analysis with incorrect model:

r=runDating(tree,dates,algo='BactDating',model='poisson')
print(r)
## Result from BactDating, model poisson, clock rate 10.52, relaxation parameter 0.00, root date 2008.69

Validation analysis:

postdistpvals(r,showPlot = T)
